# Smoke Test Catalog

Read when: adding a new workflow that needs smoke coverage, or a packet references a Smoke ID.
Skip when: no smoke surface is touched.

Purpose: registry of smoke tests by ID so packets and traceability rows can reference stable names instead of duplicating commands.

## Rules
- Every core workflow requires at least one smoke or documented N/A rationale.
- Smoke tests should run in seconds.
- New smoke test rows are added in the same packet that introduces the workflow.
- Path ID rows reference Smoke IDs or smoke commands.

## Naming
- `SMOKE-<SCOPE>-<NN>` such as `SMOKE-AUTH-01`, `SMOKE-CLI-01`

## Current Smoke Tests

| Smoke ID | Test File / Step | Purpose | Trigger Command |
|---|---|---|---|
| SMOKE-VERIFY-01 | verify gate | Project invariants | `[VERIFY_COMMAND]` |

## Adding A New Smoke Test
1. Write a fast pass/fail check.
2. Add a row above.
3. Reference it from affected Path IDs.
4. Worker runs it before returning DONE.
